1
00:00:00,340 --> 00:00:01,540
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,540 --> 00:00:03,380
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,440 --> 00:00:05,180
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:06,780 --> 00:00:08,780
Let go, darn it.

5
00:00:09,850 --> 00:00:11,220
(Episode 27)

6
00:00:13,320 --> 00:00:14,990
So now you're resorting to robbery?

7
00:00:15,650 --> 00:00:17,120
Get your hands off what's mine.

8
00:00:18,190 --> 00:00:20,330
That's rich, coming from the one
who snuck in here like a thief.

9
00:00:21,290 --> 00:00:23,460
I'll report you for ignoring
the chairman's orders...

10
00:00:23,460 --> 00:00:26,000
and trying to sneak this out.

11
00:00:26,100 --> 00:00:28,600
What? You'll report me?

12
00:00:30,300 --> 00:00:32,740
Go on. I dare you.

13
00:01:03,770 --> 00:01:07,670
Is Oh Jung Ran nuts?
How could she bite you?

14
00:01:08,810 --> 00:01:11,240
It must've been something
she couldn't afford to lose.

15
00:01:14,980 --> 00:01:17,720
(2019, Eunhwa Trading,
Seo Yi Bon, No. 5)

16
00:01:17,920 --> 00:01:20,990
You said it was a kind of notebook.

17
00:01:21,920 --> 00:01:23,790
Could it be linked
to a slush fund ledger?

18
00:01:24,860 --> 00:01:27,860
Chairman Park probably manages
the slush fund ledger himself.

19
00:01:28,930 --> 00:01:30,160
Instead of a slush fund,

20
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:33,000
I think this refers to a painting
that was traded.

21
00:01:33,730 --> 00:01:36,500
You mean a record of bribes
coming from the gallery?

22
00:01:37,470 --> 00:01:41,110
For now, look into Eunhwa Trading
and the paintings by Seo Yi Bon.

23
00:01:41,640 --> 00:01:43,810
Okay. I'll be discreet about it.

24
00:01:45,580 --> 00:01:49,810
But... Why 2019, of all years?

25
00:01:50,520 --> 00:01:51,850
The year 2019?

26
00:01:52,650 --> 00:01:56,020
That's when the Temi Bio
and Dr. Baek incident happened.

27
00:02:00,960 --> 00:02:03,060
(2019, Eunhwa Trading,
Seo Yi Bon, No. 5)

28
00:02:07,900 --> 00:02:10,340
You darn fool. Unbelievable.

29
00:02:11,570 --> 00:02:13,270
I told you to keep watch.
You couldn't even do that?

30
00:02:13,770 --> 00:02:16,370
You got me caught by Kim Myung Hui!
I nearly had a heart attack.

31
00:02:16,570 --> 00:02:18,540
I called,

32
00:02:18,540 --> 00:02:21,310
- but you didn't answer.
- As if you called me.

33
00:02:23,480 --> 00:02:24,480
My phone.

34
00:02:26,080 --> 00:02:28,590
That Chloe, or whatever,
stole it, remember?

35
00:02:28,820 --> 00:02:31,190
Right. She did, didn't she?

36
00:02:31,690 --> 00:02:33,320
"She did, didn't she?"

37
00:02:34,390 --> 00:02:36,760
If you couldn't reach me,
you should've come inside!

38
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:39,200
Kim Myung Hui nearly snatched it
from me.

39
00:02:39,630 --> 00:02:41,370
What were you in there to grab?

40
00:02:43,700 --> 00:02:44,770
A ledger.

41
00:02:46,170 --> 00:02:49,370
If there's one thing I'm good at,
it's keeping track of money.

42
00:02:50,070 --> 00:02:52,010
Tae Ho controls
the slush fund ledger,

43
00:02:52,010 --> 00:02:53,140
so I can't touch it.

44
00:02:53,880 --> 00:02:56,280
But I wrote down who I paid,

45
00:02:56,580 --> 00:02:59,450
and exactly when and how much.

46
00:03:00,990 --> 00:03:04,690
You mean that thing you scribbled in
so you won't pay the same guy twice?

47
00:03:05,290 --> 00:03:06,820
And here I thought
it was something important.

48
00:03:07,590 --> 00:03:10,960
What can you do with an errand log
for Chairman Park?

49
00:03:11,300 --> 00:03:12,960
I'm going to make a few things
perfectly clear.

50
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:16,170
Just how much dirty work
I've done for Park Tae Ho,

51
00:03:16,170 --> 00:03:18,370
and how many of his secrets
I'm sitting on.

52
00:03:19,170 --> 00:03:22,610
I'll threaten him a little,
and say it's a ticking time bomb.

53
00:03:23,340 --> 00:03:25,040
That'll make him think twice
about keeping me...

54
00:03:25,640 --> 00:03:27,210
and this ledger out of the house.

55
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:29,580
That's my way back in.

56
00:03:32,450 --> 00:03:33,990
- Good grief.
- Let's scram.

57
00:03:34,750 --> 00:03:36,820
I'm so sick and tired of this.

58
00:03:37,660 --> 00:03:39,720
- Slow down. We might trip.
- Hurry up.

59
00:03:44,160 --> 00:03:45,730
(Consultant, Chloe Lee)

60
00:03:49,070 --> 00:03:50,270
Can we talk for a second?

61
00:03:51,170 --> 00:03:52,170
What about?

62
00:03:54,570 --> 00:03:56,310
Do you feel guilty
for backing out...

63
00:03:56,980 --> 00:03:58,940
after you said
we'd handle this together?

64
00:04:00,810 --> 00:04:03,110
I'm sorry about that.

65
00:04:03,850 --> 00:04:07,290
- I'm sure that was upsetting.
- Forget it.

66
00:04:08,220 --> 00:04:11,820
I knew you couldn't stand up
to the chairman.

67
00:04:12,860 --> 00:04:15,530
That's why I made a deal with him.

68
00:04:16,190 --> 00:04:19,060
The case will be closed
with Choi Yu Na's dismissal.

69
00:04:19,300 --> 00:04:20,370
Then,

70
00:04:21,370 --> 00:04:22,830
can we talk about us?

71
00:04:24,870 --> 00:04:25,940
Us?

72
00:04:29,840 --> 00:04:31,680
What made you say that
in the basement storage room?

73
00:04:32,510 --> 00:04:34,150
In that critical moment,

74
00:04:35,910 --> 00:04:38,520
you called me
as if I were a close friend.

75
00:04:40,150 --> 00:04:41,990
Why did you call me like that?

76
00:04:49,890 --> 00:04:51,230
Don't even think about
avoiding the question.

77
00:04:52,460 --> 00:04:54,200
Because I heard you loud and clear.

78
00:05:10,080 --> 00:05:11,550
I was about to leave,

79
00:05:14,790 --> 00:05:16,390
but it sounded like
you two were arguing,

80
00:05:17,290 --> 00:05:18,660
so I couldn't just walk away.

81
00:05:20,990 --> 00:05:23,560
What's got you two so serious?

82
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:27,700
Chloe, answer me.

83
00:05:32,900 --> 00:05:34,070
Don't tell me you still think...

84
00:05:36,070 --> 00:05:37,780
I'm that woman who died.

85
00:05:40,340 --> 00:05:43,920
You really can't let it go, can you?

86
00:05:45,420 --> 00:05:48,490
Now you're just making things up.

87
00:05:53,490 --> 00:05:54,830
Knock it off.

88
00:05:55,860 --> 00:05:56,860
Let go of me.

89
00:05:58,030 --> 00:06:00,570
This is between Chloe and me.

90
00:06:00,630 --> 00:06:04,040
Exactly.
She's Chloe, plain and simple.

91
00:06:04,370 --> 00:06:06,300
You already have your answer.
Stop dwelling on it.

92
00:06:07,510 --> 00:06:10,880
It looks like you're trying
to force Chloe to be Baek Jin Ju.

93
00:06:32,300 --> 00:06:33,300
Chloe.

94
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:35,200
Are you leaving for the day?

95
00:06:36,130 --> 00:06:38,700
How about that "heavy dinner"
we talked about?

96
00:06:39,740 --> 00:06:40,940
Given what happened
with my mom and all,

97
00:06:41,270 --> 00:06:42,970
this one's on me.

98
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:46,840
I had so much to deal with
after that false accusation case.

99
00:06:48,050 --> 00:06:50,150
I'd really just like to rest today.

100
00:06:59,160 --> 00:07:00,160
Choi Yu Na?

101
00:07:02,190 --> 00:07:03,760
She's still hanging around.

102
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:16,270
Choi Yu Na!

103
00:07:19,210 --> 00:07:20,750
The article
about the design book theft.

104
00:07:21,650 --> 00:07:22,750
That was you, wasn't it?

105
00:07:24,280 --> 00:07:26,050
You got me fired,

106
00:07:27,220 --> 00:07:28,220
didn't you?

107
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:37,530
Get your facts straight.

108
00:07:39,030 --> 00:07:41,230
The article isn't
what got you fired.

109
00:07:42,230 --> 00:07:45,670
Chairman Park Tae Ho's decision did.

110
00:07:47,410 --> 00:07:48,740
If you're that angry
and feel wronged,

111
00:07:49,340 --> 00:07:52,340
you should take it up
with Chairman Park.

112
00:07:56,010 --> 00:07:57,010
What's the matter?

113
00:07:59,780 --> 00:08:02,990
Are you that scared of him?

114
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:08,090
Are you too much of a coward
to even put up a fight?

115
00:08:10,030 --> 00:08:11,030
You...

116
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:14,030
- You...
- If you don't have the guts...

117
00:08:14,030 --> 00:08:15,230
to fight back,

118
00:08:16,630 --> 00:08:18,740
just accept
that you've been tossed aside.

119
00:08:20,270 --> 00:08:23,470
It's a fitting end
for a coward like you.

120
00:08:29,550 --> 00:08:30,550
Chloe.

121
00:08:39,990 --> 00:08:41,660
Who is she calling a coward?

122
00:08:44,860 --> 00:08:46,530
After everything I've done
to get this far?

123
00:08:52,470 --> 00:08:53,470
Just you wait.

124
00:08:54,670 --> 00:08:55,940
I'll prove...

125
00:08:57,440 --> 00:09:00,110
that Chairman Park
can never cast me aside.

126
00:09:16,460 --> 00:09:17,460
- Sir.
- Sir.

127
00:09:24,400 --> 00:09:26,170
- You can't do this to me.
- You can't do this to me!

128
00:09:30,840 --> 00:09:34,280
Hanging out together has made
you both equally pathetic.

129
00:09:34,450 --> 00:09:36,050
- Get them out of here.
- Yes, sir.

130
00:09:37,150 --> 00:09:39,450
- I have a secret ledger.
- Did you forget about Temi Bio?

131
00:09:42,890 --> 00:09:44,920
What? Temi Bio?

132
00:09:45,120 --> 00:09:46,220
A secret ledger?

133
00:09:46,620 --> 00:09:49,430
Take Ms. Choi to my study.

134
00:09:49,530 --> 00:09:50,590
Yes, sir.

135
00:10:18,490 --> 00:10:19,790
A secret ledger?

136
00:10:20,220 --> 00:10:22,330
And Temi Bio?

137
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,470
Ms. Choi, why are you here?

138
00:10:34,140 --> 00:10:36,470
I was waiting because I heard
the chairman was on his way.

139
00:10:37,170 --> 00:10:38,210
Where is he?

140
00:10:39,880 --> 00:10:41,350
He'll be in shortly.

141
00:10:41,980 --> 00:10:44,680
He said he had something
to discuss privately with Ms. Choi.

142
00:10:45,220 --> 00:10:46,250
Now, if you'll excuse us.

143
00:10:47,390 --> 00:10:50,790
Let go of me. I can walk on my own.

144
00:11:15,150 --> 00:11:16,480
A secret ledger?

145
00:11:17,080 --> 00:11:18,080
That...

146
00:11:18,550 --> 00:11:19,580
That's right.

147
00:11:19,950 --> 00:11:23,790
I wrote down every piece
of dirty work you had me do,

148
00:11:24,420 --> 00:11:27,790
including all the hush money
and every bribe you paid out.

149
00:11:29,590 --> 00:11:30,590
So?

150
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:35,730
Think about
how important I am to you.

151
00:11:36,230 --> 00:11:38,600
I'm sitting on all those secrets.

152
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:40,470
Are you really going
to let them get out?

153
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:44,440
And you think
all those secrets are mine?

154
00:11:44,810 --> 00:11:46,380
You caused all those problems...

155
00:11:46,680 --> 00:11:49,180
and paid bribes
to keep everything under wraps.

156
00:11:49,850 --> 00:11:52,520
That makes them all your secrets,
doesn't it?

157
00:11:52,950 --> 00:11:53,950
Honey.

158
00:11:59,220 --> 00:12:00,930
There's no way...

159
00:12:01,830 --> 00:12:04,400
that pathetic book proves
I forced you to do anything.

160
00:12:05,230 --> 00:12:09,530
Those are payments from your gallery
that you authorized.

161
00:12:09,800 --> 00:12:11,100
If this becomes a problem,

162
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:15,370
you'll pay the price, not me.

163
00:12:17,510 --> 00:12:18,510
And of course,

164
00:12:19,810 --> 00:12:22,650
it will ruin Hyun Jun's future too.

165
00:12:23,910 --> 00:12:26,050
Even Hyun Jun?

166
00:12:26,650 --> 00:12:27,650
Honey.

167
00:12:27,790 --> 00:12:30,450
If you understand, wait quietly.

168
00:12:31,720 --> 00:12:34,630
I'll call when I find a use for you,
all right?

169
00:12:35,790 --> 00:12:37,330
What if you don't find a use for me?

170
00:12:38,030 --> 00:12:39,800
Does that mean
you'll get rid of me for good?

171
00:12:42,170 --> 00:12:43,170
Darn.

172
00:12:43,330 --> 00:12:44,740
Then what about Kim Myung Hui?

173
00:12:48,970 --> 00:12:51,810
What makes that tramp so useful
that you're always doting on her?

174
00:12:53,310 --> 00:12:55,180
You treat me like trash
to be thrown away...

175
00:12:55,180 --> 00:12:57,010
and picked up again, so why not her?

176
00:12:57,310 --> 00:12:59,420
Why haven't you ever
pushed her aside?

177
00:13:13,860 --> 00:13:14,970
You're back, sir.

178
00:13:17,230 --> 00:13:21,070
I heard you had a private meeting
with Ms. Choi, so I made tea.

179
00:13:27,710 --> 00:13:29,910
What happened to your arm?

180
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:35,020
Your wife snuck into the annex.

181
00:13:35,390 --> 00:13:39,760
She tried to leave with something.
When I stopped her, she bit me.

182
00:13:40,590 --> 00:13:41,690
She bit you?

183
00:13:45,100 --> 00:13:46,130
Are you okay?

184
00:13:46,660 --> 00:13:48,570
I'm fine. Don't worry.

185
00:13:48,830 --> 00:13:51,040
- The tea is getting cold.
- Never mind the tea.

186
00:13:52,540 --> 00:13:54,810
I need to speak
with Ms. Choi in private,

187
00:13:55,470 --> 00:13:56,610
so you can go get some rest.

188
00:14:15,790 --> 00:14:18,700
Ms. Choi definitely
mentioned Temi Bio.

189
00:14:19,160 --> 00:14:22,370
What kind of secret
are those two hiding?

190
00:14:29,010 --> 00:14:30,610
Reinstate me right now.

191
00:14:32,380 --> 00:14:36,410
If I'm not with Adele anymore,
I've no reason to keep your secret.

192
00:14:37,980 --> 00:14:38,980
My secret?

193
00:14:41,350 --> 00:14:43,420
Baek Jun Gi, the CEO of Temi Bio.

194
00:14:44,490 --> 00:14:47,460
I could expose your secret
to the whole world.

195
00:14:51,960 --> 00:14:53,760
Unbelievable.

196
00:14:59,840 --> 00:15:03,410
You dare to threaten me?

197
00:15:03,740 --> 00:15:06,280
CEO Baek Jun Gi of Temi Bio?

198
00:15:07,580 --> 00:15:12,320
Before you utter his name,
you should remember how he died.

199
00:15:12,420 --> 00:15:13,580
Remember...

200
00:15:13,650 --> 00:15:17,720
how I deal with people
who get in my way.

201
00:15:21,760 --> 00:15:25,900
I went easy on you not out of fear,
but because you were easy to handle.

202
00:15:26,330 --> 00:15:29,470
Easy to use and throw away.

203
00:15:43,780 --> 00:15:47,750
When I decide to get rid of you,
you're supposed to just go quietly.

204
00:15:48,450 --> 00:15:51,960
If you get cocky and run your mouth,

205
00:15:54,060 --> 00:15:58,330
I might release
your recorded confession.

206
00:15:59,400 --> 00:16:01,030
It definitely feels
like a good option.

207
00:16:03,600 --> 00:16:04,840
And on top of that,

208
00:16:05,370 --> 00:16:07,710
you've admitted
to being an accomplice...

209
00:16:09,470 --> 00:16:11,180
to murder.

210
00:16:16,250 --> 00:16:18,820
It will be far more agonizing...

211
00:16:19,150 --> 00:16:21,320
and brutal than being burned alive.

212
00:16:21,920 --> 00:16:24,520
I, Park Tae Ho,

213
00:16:25,760 --> 00:16:28,690
give you my word.

214
00:16:53,850 --> 00:16:55,850
More agonizing
than being burned alive?

215
00:16:59,660 --> 00:17:00,690
Am I supposed...

216
00:17:01,960 --> 00:17:03,890
to be thrown away like this?

217
00:17:24,010 --> 00:17:25,020
Is that so?

218
00:17:25,380 --> 00:17:27,890
Okay, got it. Thanks. Good work.

219
00:17:34,360 --> 00:17:35,430
Choi Yu Na.

220
00:17:36,560 --> 00:17:39,300
Looks like she left his house
completely shaken.

221
00:17:40,500 --> 00:17:43,930
She must snap
and kill Chairman Park,

222
00:17:45,040 --> 00:17:48,440
and he must take her down in turn.

223
00:17:50,140 --> 00:17:51,980
To get the ending I want,

224
00:17:52,480 --> 00:17:54,880
they have to fight relentlessly.

225
00:17:56,750 --> 00:18:00,620
But if Choi Yu Na backs down,
there won't be a fight.

226
00:18:03,350 --> 00:18:05,320
Is confronting Chairman Park...

227
00:18:06,920 --> 00:18:08,230
really that difficult?

228
00:18:10,390 --> 00:18:12,430
For someone like her,
it could be even harder.

229
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:16,370
Remember, she knows exactly
how Chairman Park...

230
00:18:17,570 --> 00:18:18,800
killed Dr. Baek.

231
00:18:22,070 --> 00:18:25,340
That's all the more reason
to push her...

232
00:18:25,840 --> 00:18:28,080
and put a weapon in her hand
so she'll fight.

233
00:18:29,080 --> 00:18:32,850
I'll see if I can find
one of Chairman Park's weaknesses...

234
00:18:34,280 --> 00:18:35,690
to leak to her.

235
00:18:41,390 --> 00:18:43,730
(Choi Yu Na)

236
00:18:58,010 --> 00:18:59,010
(Bongmyeong Neighborhood Coffee)

237
00:18:59,810 --> 00:19:02,180
Look at him, worrying again today.

238
00:19:02,880 --> 00:19:04,980
Doesn't he have friends
he can drink with?

239
00:19:12,320 --> 00:19:14,690
Hey, why have you been looking
so serious?

240
00:19:17,060 --> 00:19:18,460
It's just...

241
00:19:20,230 --> 00:19:22,230
Think of me
as your friendly cafe owner...

242
00:19:22,800 --> 00:19:25,340
or a neighborhood friend,
and feel free to unload.

243
00:19:25,870 --> 00:19:28,570
Sometimes it helps
to get things off your chest.

244
00:19:34,080 --> 00:19:36,080
I wanted to be absolutely sure.

245
00:19:38,220 --> 00:19:39,950
I was worried...

246
00:19:40,550 --> 00:19:44,120
my desperation was clouding
my judgment,

247
00:19:44,220 --> 00:19:45,960
so I kept second-guessing
everything.

248
00:19:47,690 --> 00:19:48,760
But...

249
00:19:50,060 --> 00:19:51,190
I just don't know anymore.

250
00:19:53,530 --> 00:19:57,330
You really can't let it go, can you?

251
00:19:58,540 --> 00:20:01,810
Now you're just making things up.

252
00:20:03,740 --> 00:20:05,610
I thought I was certain,

253
00:20:06,040 --> 00:20:07,640
but was it just wishful thinking?

254
00:20:07,640 --> 00:20:09,280
I thought
I was confirming my suspicion,

255
00:20:10,880 --> 00:20:12,950
but was I just forcing the issue?

256
00:20:14,520 --> 00:20:18,090
I don't know what I was doing
or what I'm supposed to do.

257
00:20:19,320 --> 00:20:20,420
I just don't know anymore.

258
00:20:21,660 --> 00:20:23,560
You were certain,
and you were confirming it.

259
00:20:25,530 --> 00:20:27,500
I don't know the whole situation,

260
00:20:27,700 --> 00:20:29,230
but I'm a pretty good judge
of character.

261
00:20:29,930 --> 00:20:34,070
And you don't seem like the type
to delude yourself or force things.

262
00:20:35,040 --> 00:20:37,910
So trust yourself and keep at it,
whatever it is.

263
00:20:39,510 --> 00:20:40,610
It's okay.

264
00:20:56,790 --> 00:20:57,790
Hyun Jun.

265
00:20:58,500 --> 00:20:59,930
Why are you here?

266
00:20:59,930 --> 00:21:01,400
Is this how it's going to be?

267
00:21:02,100 --> 00:21:03,670
I know you're mad,

268
00:21:03,670 --> 00:21:06,200
but how could you not even try
to reach me or call me?

269
00:21:06,840 --> 00:21:09,970
Even now,
you don't even ask how I'm doing.

270
00:21:10,110 --> 00:21:12,110
I knew you'd manage just fine.

271
00:21:12,180 --> 00:21:14,710
How can I be fine when I've been
kicked out of my own home?

272
00:21:16,250 --> 00:21:18,020
So what do you want me
to do about it?

273
00:21:19,580 --> 00:21:22,420
You need to convince your father
to cut me some slack.

274
00:21:23,020 --> 00:21:26,520
Like I always say,
it's every man for himself.

275
00:21:27,660 --> 00:21:29,130
Handle it yourself, Mom.

276
00:21:30,230 --> 00:21:31,460
You think I haven't tried?

277
00:21:31,830 --> 00:21:34,200
I'm asking
because nothing has worked.

278
00:21:35,630 --> 00:21:38,770
I knew your father was cold,
but this is just cruel.

279
00:21:39,340 --> 00:21:42,740
He can't do this to me
after everything I've done for him.

280
00:21:43,070 --> 00:21:45,480
How can he act like this
just because I went a bit overboard?

281
00:21:45,580 --> 00:21:47,810
You still don't feel any remorse,
do you?

282
00:21:48,850 --> 00:21:51,550
- Hyun Jun!
- I'm still not over it,

283
00:21:51,880 --> 00:21:54,280
and you still don't seem to get
what the problem is,

284
00:21:54,350 --> 00:21:56,550
which means you're not ready
to come home yet.

285
00:21:56,650 --> 00:21:57,690
Ms. Oh,

286
00:21:58,820 --> 00:22:01,290
while you're on your own,
think about what you did.

287
00:22:01,730 --> 00:22:04,900
This might even be
a good experience for you.

288
00:22:05,800 --> 00:22:08,730
Hyun Jun, wait. Park Hyun Jun.

289
00:22:09,870 --> 00:22:11,740
Hyun Jun, come on.

290
00:22:12,370 --> 00:22:14,240
Open this door.

291
00:22:14,240 --> 00:22:16,710
Hyun Jun, are you really
going to do this to me?

292
00:22:16,770 --> 00:22:17,840
Hey, Hyun Jun!

293
00:22:19,840 --> 00:22:21,010
Hey!

294
00:22:24,280 --> 00:22:26,480
They say a rotten husband
makes for rotten children.

295
00:22:27,150 --> 00:22:29,420
That heartless Park family!

296
00:22:31,520 --> 00:22:33,420
How can no one be on my side?

297
00:22:42,330 --> 00:22:45,170
Why are you on my bed?
Get off right now.

298
00:22:45,870 --> 00:22:48,140
Why are you fussing
over a stupid bed?

299
00:22:49,170 --> 00:22:51,170
Looks like your blackmail failed.

300
00:22:54,010 --> 00:22:56,180
Aren't you the one who got burned?

301
00:22:57,050 --> 00:22:58,650
You talked a big game
about a secret ledger.

302
00:23:00,050 --> 00:23:02,050
I guess it was just
a worthless piece of paper.

303
00:23:02,390 --> 00:23:03,650
Look who's talking.

304
00:23:04,050 --> 00:23:05,220
Why did you get kicked out...

305
00:23:05,220 --> 00:23:07,560
when you tried to threaten him
with Temi Bio?

306
00:23:07,990 --> 00:23:11,090
Threatening the chairman
can get you fired, you know.

307
00:23:14,460 --> 00:23:16,730
Wait, you already got fired?

308
00:23:19,770 --> 00:23:22,840
Drop the attitude, you freeloader.
Get out.

309
00:23:23,070 --> 00:23:24,980
I said get off my bed!

310
00:23:25,040 --> 00:23:26,780
How dare you grab me?

311
00:23:26,780 --> 00:23:28,710
Let go, darn it.

312
00:23:30,310 --> 00:23:32,780
Seriously? You have some nerve.

313
00:23:33,050 --> 00:23:36,890
Who do you think
you're messing with?

314
00:23:36,950 --> 00:23:38,020
- Jung Ran!
- Yu Na!

315
00:23:39,290 --> 00:23:41,160
What's all this ruckus?

316
00:23:41,220 --> 00:23:43,030
Jung Ran, please!

317
00:23:43,090 --> 00:23:46,230
Why do you keep doing this
when you have nowhere else to go?

318
00:23:46,300 --> 00:23:49,330
She's taking it out on me
because she got fired!

319
00:23:49,700 --> 00:23:50,870
I know, but still...

320
00:23:52,040 --> 00:23:53,470
You got fired?

321
00:23:53,770 --> 00:23:55,410
Is that true?

322
00:23:56,340 --> 00:23:58,580
Get out right now!

323
00:23:58,580 --> 00:23:59,610
You little brat.

324
00:24:00,680 --> 00:24:02,450
- Let's go. Come on.
- What on earth?

325
00:24:04,480 --> 00:24:06,280
Honestly.

326
00:24:16,990 --> 00:24:19,300
(Adele)

327
00:24:19,900 --> 00:24:20,900
What?

328
00:24:21,230 --> 00:24:25,770
Wait, you're curious
about the Temi Bio acquisition?

329
00:24:27,140 --> 00:24:29,110
Why bring that up all of a sudden?

330
00:24:29,440 --> 00:24:31,140
As the head of the bio division,

331
00:24:31,640 --> 00:24:33,140
I need to be aware of its history.

332
00:24:34,240 --> 00:24:35,510
Were the acquisition negotiations...

333
00:24:35,880 --> 00:24:38,480
handled by CEO Baek Jun Gi?

334
00:24:39,020 --> 00:24:40,050
Sorry?

335
00:24:40,750 --> 00:24:42,720
Oh, that.

336
00:24:42,820 --> 00:24:44,690
I was the one who initiated it.

337
00:24:45,220 --> 00:24:47,620
Chairman Park made a proposal.

338
00:24:48,860 --> 00:24:50,360
The chairman approached you first?

339
00:24:50,690 --> 00:24:55,170
What role did Ms. Oh Jung Ran play
in the acquisition?

340
00:24:55,730 --> 00:24:56,870
Ms. Oh?

341
00:24:57,700 --> 00:25:00,700
Gosh, I didn't even know
who she was back then.

342
00:25:01,400 --> 00:25:04,340
I first met her the day
she showed up at my house...

343
00:25:06,310 --> 00:25:07,410
and started pulling my wife's hair.

344
00:25:08,450 --> 00:25:09,450
Is that so?

345
00:25:15,590 --> 00:25:19,320
We may have rushed things
after CEO Baek's accident,

346
00:25:19,820 --> 00:25:22,560
but there were no issues
with the acquisition process itself.

347
00:25:24,430 --> 00:25:25,430
I see.

348
00:25:26,060 --> 00:25:27,060
Understood.

349
00:25:29,100 --> 00:25:30,100
One more thing.

350
00:25:30,900 --> 00:25:33,070
How is Ms. Choi holding up?

351
00:25:33,340 --> 00:25:35,140
You're aware
that she was fired, right?

352
00:25:37,110 --> 00:25:41,040
As a matter of fact,
things at home have been terrible.

353
00:25:41,440 --> 00:25:43,510
To be honest, when you contacted me,

354
00:25:44,750 --> 00:25:47,650
I was hoping you'd want
to discuss Yu Na's situation.

355
00:25:49,090 --> 00:25:51,890
Please give my daughter
a second chance.

356
00:25:52,820 --> 00:25:53,820
I'm not so sure.

357
00:25:54,220 --> 00:25:56,360
I thought I already
gave her a break.

358
00:25:56,890 --> 00:26:00,000
After all, the case was closed
without involving the police.

359
00:26:04,500 --> 00:26:08,640
But if you're that worried,
you can always talk to the chairman.

360
00:26:09,370 --> 00:26:11,640
Ms. Choi and the chairman...

361
00:26:12,080 --> 00:26:14,710
go way back to their Temi Bio days,
don't they?

362
00:26:15,780 --> 00:26:17,710
Yu Na and the chairman?

363
00:26:18,980 --> 00:26:22,650
She only met him once back then,

364
00:26:23,290 --> 00:26:25,620
at the design contest
award ceremony.

365
00:26:25,790 --> 00:26:27,360
She spent years studying abroad,

366
00:26:27,660 --> 00:26:29,990
and she hasn't been
at Adele very long.

367
00:26:30,290 --> 00:26:32,630
It's not like they have much history
to fall back on.

368
00:26:33,830 --> 00:26:35,300
Please don't be like this.

369
00:26:35,900 --> 00:26:37,170
I'd really appreciate it...

370
00:26:37,430 --> 00:26:40,140
if you could pull some strings
for her.

371
00:26:46,110 --> 00:26:47,110
Hello.

372
00:26:53,380 --> 00:26:57,320
So, is she going to help
Yu Na or not?

373
00:26:58,490 --> 00:27:02,790
I came here to talk about Yu Na,
and she grilled me about Temi Bio.

374
00:27:03,030 --> 00:27:04,690
What about Temi Bio?

375
00:27:16,470 --> 00:27:19,410
So, what did you think
of Choi Sam Sik?

376
00:27:20,040 --> 00:27:21,340
Back during the Temi Bio incident,

377
00:27:21,340 --> 00:27:23,280
do you think
there was something going on...

378
00:27:23,550 --> 00:27:25,380
between the chairman and Ms. Choi?

379
00:27:26,250 --> 00:27:28,320
Mr. Choi's a terrible liar,

380
00:27:28,820 --> 00:27:30,920
and he seemed clueless
about their relationship.

381
00:27:31,420 --> 00:27:32,420
So,

382
00:27:32,790 --> 00:27:36,230
do Chairman Park and Ms. Choi have
a secret of their own?

383
00:27:37,060 --> 00:27:38,400
How could...

384
00:27:38,860 --> 00:27:41,130
the two of them have a secret
involving Temi Bio?

385
00:27:51,540 --> 00:27:53,410
I heard you met with Choi Sam Sik.

386
00:27:55,980 --> 00:27:56,980
Yes.

387
00:27:58,950 --> 00:28:00,480
Was it to discuss Ms. Choi?

388
00:28:03,820 --> 00:28:08,760
I met him to confirm details
about the Temi Bio acquisition.

389
00:28:10,290 --> 00:28:12,900
Why are you bringing that up
all of a sudden?

390
00:28:16,770 --> 00:28:18,640
When Ms. Choi came to the house,

391
00:28:18,940 --> 00:28:20,540
she said something strange.

392
00:28:22,010 --> 00:28:24,340
It sounded like she was involved...

393
00:28:24,870 --> 00:28:26,710
in the Temi Bio acquisition.

394
00:28:27,310 --> 00:28:29,750
How could Ms. Choi
have been involved?

395
00:28:30,210 --> 00:28:34,580
That's what I found strange,
so I wanted to confirm it.

396
00:28:34,720 --> 00:28:37,220
Then you should have asked me first.

397
00:28:38,350 --> 00:28:39,360
Why?

398
00:28:40,320 --> 00:28:41,620
Did you think...

399
00:28:42,730 --> 00:28:45,800
I wouldn't give you a straight answer
if you asked me?

400
00:28:47,100 --> 00:28:48,800
Is it because you don't trust me?

401
00:28:57,310 --> 00:29:00,410
If I didn't trust you,

402
00:29:01,310 --> 00:29:02,650
how could I...

403
00:29:03,150 --> 00:29:05,550
have been with you
for the last 30 years?

404
00:29:07,250 --> 00:29:08,450
It's just that...

405
00:29:08,650 --> 00:29:11,090
you get so uncomfortable
whenever Temi Bio comes up,

406
00:29:11,890 --> 00:29:13,990
so I tried to look into it
on my own.

407
00:29:17,890 --> 00:29:20,860
So you were just being careful
for my sake?

408
00:29:22,900 --> 00:29:24,830
Right, Myung Hui,

409
00:29:26,200 --> 00:29:28,470
you of all people
shouldn't mistrust me.

410
00:29:38,680 --> 00:29:42,090
Ma'am, you need to be
at the women entrepreneurs' meeting,

411
00:29:42,390 --> 00:29:43,620
and we need to leave now.

412
00:30:07,540 --> 00:30:10,980
Choi Yu Na...
What exactly did you let slip?

413
00:30:13,120 --> 00:30:16,650
Still, how dare she try to dig
into Temi Bio behind my back?

414
00:30:18,720 --> 00:30:21,560
Is Kim Myung Hui
trying to cross a line...

415
00:30:22,960 --> 00:30:24,230
I've drawn?

416
00:30:29,630 --> 00:30:32,540
You should've just lied and said
you met because of Ms. Choi.

417
00:30:33,670 --> 00:30:36,840
He would've been more suspicious
if I'd made up an excuse.

418
00:30:37,470 --> 00:30:39,640
Still, Chairman Park's expression
really worries me.

419
00:30:40,380 --> 00:30:43,050
He got so scary the moment
you brought up Temi Bio.

420
00:30:43,710 --> 00:30:44,710
Just as I suspected,

421
00:30:45,720 --> 00:30:48,550
there's definitely something
between Chairman Park and Ms. Choi.

422
00:30:50,620 --> 00:30:52,660
We'll have to keep digging
into her background.

423
00:30:53,460 --> 00:30:55,430
Also, speed up the investigation
into Eunhwa Trading...

424
00:30:55,530 --> 00:30:57,360
based on Oh Jung Ran's ledger.

425
00:30:58,290 --> 00:30:59,300
Got it.

426
00:30:59,700 --> 00:31:01,700
We'd better get going
if we don't want to be late.

427
00:31:02,070 --> 00:31:04,300
It's your first time
at the Women's Business Association,

428
00:31:04,600 --> 00:31:05,840
so we can't be late.

429
00:31:18,650 --> 00:31:19,650
That's so true.

430
00:31:20,650 --> 00:31:22,320
- Yes.
- Right.

431
00:31:22,950 --> 00:31:25,660
My gosh, what is she doing here?

432
00:31:27,320 --> 00:31:28,960
Goodness, no way.

433
00:31:28,960 --> 00:31:30,630
I know, the nerve of her to come.

434
00:31:30,690 --> 00:31:31,690
Exactly.

435
00:31:32,700 --> 00:31:33,930
Honestly, she has no shame.

436
00:31:34,500 --> 00:31:35,500
Seriously.

437
00:31:54,620 --> 00:31:56,790
- Oh my.
- My gosh!

438
00:31:56,920 --> 00:31:57,920
Goodness.

439
00:32:02,860 --> 00:32:03,860
What now?

440
00:32:14,600 --> 00:32:16,440
I've taken care of it
as you instructed.

441
00:32:20,780 --> 00:32:21,780
Good.

442
00:32:22,680 --> 00:32:24,410
She'll pay...

443
00:32:25,580 --> 00:32:28,950
for going behind my back
and crossing the line.

444
00:32:55,450 --> 00:32:58,550
(Pearl in Red)

445
00:32:58,750 --> 00:33:00,150
I've taken care of it
as you instructed.

446
00:33:00,250 --> 00:33:02,220
Am I just his puppet and scapegoat?

447
00:33:02,220 --> 00:33:04,220
How could he use me like this?

448
00:33:04,320 --> 00:33:08,660
I have to find a way to protect
my future from Chairman Park.

449
00:33:08,890 --> 00:33:10,730
I'll claim my place
as the lady of Adele...

450
00:33:10,730 --> 00:33:12,630
and show them all what I'm made of.

451
00:33:12,630 --> 00:33:14,600
- Ma'am!
- Jung Ran!

452
00:33:16,900 --> 00:33:18,570
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
